text.en_US: Actually, this won't be implemented until a later XPC update. The quest doesn't exist yet.

message.en_US: I think that was the last of them!
I managed to turn off my test script that kept spawning new \v[combat.name.penguin-heat]s.
Looks like you handled yourself ok. Thanks for the help!
Lea!
Hey you know...\! What did you think of them?
I'm talking about the \c[1]\v[combat.name.penguin-heat]s\c[0]. I designed their attack patterns myself.
...Lea.
Oh, is your speech module bugged? There's a mod for that, you know.
Yeah, it's an unofficial bugfix mod that's been out for a while now. You just need to download it and install it locally.
Instatainment never fixes these things, so the \c[3]modding community\c[0] fixed it themselves.
Lea!!!
Hey, why don't you come with me out of the cave? I'll introduce you to our hideout.
We can't work in the official areas, so we mostly keep to ourselves. Come, I can show you around.
I think we're about halfway there. This cave leads to a hidden area where I created the \v[combat.name.penguin-heat]s.

settings.name: TODO: Add ambient hacking effects around this area when the quest is active.

message.en_US: Oh, this is the part of the cave where I was experimenting with the \v[combat.name.penguin]\c[0] game files!
At least, that's what I was doing until they escaped.
Uh oh...\. It looks like my scripts are still active!
That means they are going to keep coming. Prepare for a fight!

settings.name: Known issue: Light FX disappears on party members if they die and respawn

message.en_US: Mods, huh?\. I'm sure I don't need to explain to you why this is a bad idea.
Crossworlds is an online game, Lea.\. Modifying the game is obviously against the terms of use.
I'm not sure how these players managed to find a secluded area to make game modifications...
I won't stop you from going with this player, but you certainly cannot just go installing mods, ok?
[nods]
It would be one thing if you were just playing the game for fun, but given our situation it would probably be best not to draw unwanted attention.
